OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1778613067
OL,3,CRobert Peston: Why Rayner wants
OL,4,CBurnham as prime minister
OL,6,FHer view is that there must be a soft-
OL,7,Fleft dog in any leadership race. And
OL,8,Fif that race was triggered by Wes
OL,9,FStreeting today or in the coming days,
OL,10,Fwhile Burnham is still outside the
OL,11,FCommons, she would feel it was her
OL,12,Fduty to be a contestant - unless, that
OL,13,Fis, another soft-left MP, such as Ed
OL,14,FMiliband, were to go for it.
OL,16,FIn a nutshell, she seems to have
OL,17,Fdecided her preferred role is to be
OL,18,Fthe maker of the king or queen, not
OL,19,Fthe monarch herself. Unless duty calls.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/4
